Use a combination chart to show multiple values against a single axis range, show two chart types together, or compare two continuous summary values.
A combination chart plots multiple sets of data on a single chart.

Column-on-Column
To show multiple values against a single axis range, add columns to a column chart.
Line-on-Column
To show two chart types together, add a line to a column chart.
Line-on-Line
To compare two continuous summary values, add a line to a line chart.
